</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-family:switzer_variableregular\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Now it is the time to look into some of the safer paths that will help you to double your money.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"padding:0px 0px 0px 20px; border:0px; font-style:normal; font-variant-ligatures:normal; font-variant-caps:normal; font-variant-numeric:inherit; font-variant-east-asian:inherit; font-variant-alternates:inherit; font-weight:400; font-stretch:inherit; font-size:18px; line-height:inherit; font-family:switzer_variableregular; font-optical-sizing:inherit; font-kerning:inherit; font-feature-settings:inherit; font-variation-settings:inherit; vertical-align:baseline; list-style:inside; box-sizing:border-box; color:#0f1418; letter-spacing:normal; orphans:2; text-align:start; text-indent:0px; text-transform:none; widows:2; word-spacing:0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; white-space:normal; background-color:#ffffff; text-decoration-thickness:initial; text-decoration-style:initial; text-decoration-color:initial; margin-bottom:15px\">\r\n\t<li style=\"padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b style=\"padding:0px; border:0px; font:inherit; vertical-align:baseline\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Debt Mutual Funds</span></span></b><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit; text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">: They are safer investment&nbsp;</span></span><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit; text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">instruments that invest in debt instruments and stocks. With an annual return of 5% to 7%, debt funds can double your money within 10 to 14 years.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b style=\"padding:0px; border:0px; font:inherit; vertical-align:baseline\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Bank Fixed Deposits</span></span></b><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit; text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">: When it comes to investments, Bank Fixed Deposits or Fixed Deposits or simply, FD are common household names. These safer investment instruments can provide annual returns of around 4% to 7% with a higher percentage of returns for senior citizens. With this rate of return, your money will double in roughly 10 to 18 years.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n\t<li style=\"padding: 0px; border: 0px; font: inherit; vertical-align: baseline; margin-bottom: 10px;\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b style=\"padding:0px; border:0px; font:inherit; vertical-align:baseline; text-indent:-18pt\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Bonds</span></span></b><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit; text-indent:-18pt\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">: Bonds are another safer investment instrument that comes with an annualized return of roughly 4% to 7% that can help you to double your money in a 10 to 18 years span.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-family:switzer_variableregular\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><b style=\"padding:0px; border:0px; font:inherit; vertical-align:baseline\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"border:0px; padding:0px; font:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#993300\">Final Thoughts</span></span></span></span></span></b></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span dir=\"rtl\"><code><q><small><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">After you have zeroed in on the investment avenue that matches with your risk profile, and your understanding of the business, you can then apply the Rule of 72 to see how much time it can take to double your money.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></small></q></code></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span dir=\"rtl\"><code><q><small><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">An intelligent investment move would be to have a mixed portfolio with riskier assets and safer assets. The function of safer assets should be to hedge the investment risks. As mentioned earlier, doubling your wealth is not an easy task within the desired timeframe. But you can turn it into a reality only if you exercise necessary vigilance, patience, a sound investment strategy, and an active involvement in tracking the performance of your portfolio.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></small></q></code></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span dir=\"rtl\"><code><q><small><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">So, always stay updated, and invest wisely.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></small></q></code></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-family:switzer_variableregular\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">&ndash; Justin Raj</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"border: 0px; padding: 1rem 0px 0px; text-indent: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-bottom: 15px;\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-numeric:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-east-asian:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant-alternates:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:1.1\"><span style=\"font-family:switzer_variableregular\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\"><span style=\"color:#0f1418\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-thickness:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span style=\"border:0px; font-size:20px; padding:0px\"><span style=\"font-style:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variant:inherit\"><span style=\"font-weight:inherit\"><span style=\"font-stretch:inherit\"><span style=\"line-height:inherit\"><span style=\"font-family:inherit\"><span style=\"font-optical-sizing:inherit\"><span style=\"font-kerning:inherit\"><span style=\"font-feature-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"font-variation-settings:inherit\"><span style=\"vertical-align:baseline\">Alpha Research Team</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687936504/heguk7o7lq2bruxpor01.webp","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"How to Double Your Investment – Get the Maths Right","seo_keywords":"How to Double Your Investment – Get the Maths Right","seo_description":"Doubling the money invested is always a big dream of every investor. Moreover, if that dream is realized in a short span, it would be an icing on the cake. Although it has been widely considered as a greedy mindset to fantasize about doubling your money, there are many ways to do so.","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687936502/kkc8ia0xumeq5dx1uqrw.webp","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"132","title":"What Are Different Ways To Invest In International Equities?","slug":"what-are-different-ways-to-invest-in-international-equities","category":"Investment Ideas","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1635837759","published_date_view":"Nov 02, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Have you ever thought of investing in globally leading innovative companies such as Apple, Google (Alphabet), Facebook, Amazon, Netflix, Microsoft, and Tesla? These international companies have greater growth potential and moreover, they are not listed in Indian stock exchanges like Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) or National Stock Exchange (NSE).</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">If you hold a dematerialized account (Demat) in India, you can trade or invest only in companies listed on Indian stock exchanges, right? Wrong. You can always buy the shares of an international company that is not registered in India and trades in a foreign stock exchange.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Investing in the international financial markets can widen the horizon of your investments. You can reap the benefits of boundless investing, that too, in your favourite companies. Moreover, in the Digital Age of high-speed internet connectivity and advanced smartphone technology, investing in international markets is not a difficult endeavour.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">This article will explore 4 simple ways to invest in international stocks. Before that, let&rsquo;s look into the reasons why Indians want to invest in International stocks in the first place.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Why Do Indians Love International Stocks?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">There are more than 5,500 listed companies in the Indian equity market. There are many Indian companies that can give tight competition to International companies. International companies like Google, Apple, Facebook, Amazon, Cisco, and Tesla hold multi-billion-dollar cash, highly qualified professionals, and bring big innovations in their respective sectors.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Anyway, are these heavy capital resources and innovations being the sole factors that attract Indian investors towards international stocks? The answer is a straightforward &lsquo;no&rsquo;.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Here are the major reasons why many Indians love to invest in stocks trading in the US or other foreign stock exchanges.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Darlings of this generation</strong>: The international companies like Apple, Google, Facebook, Amazon, and Tesla are darlings of this generation and people love to invest in their favourite companies.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>A Diversification effort</strong>: Investing in international markets and stocks helps diversification in a portfolio. Investments in a foreign stock or market can mitigate the risk of the downturn in the Indian equity market owing to some regional economic or political reasons. Apart from diversification, investing in foreign stocks would provide greater stability in a portfolio.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">​​​​​​​</span></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n\t<li><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>A limitless investing opportunity:&nbsp;</strong>International markets are a boundless investment arena with better profitable investment opportunities.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">​​​​​​​</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Now, let&rsquo;s look at the 4 simple ways to invest in foreign stocks.</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>1) Through a trading account with an Indian stock broking firm that collaborates with other international stock broking firms.</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Many full-service Indian stockbroking companies like ICICI Direct, Reliance Money, HDFC Securities, Axis Securities, and Kotak Securities collaborate with international stockbroking firms like Interactive Brokers LLC. You can easily open your overseas trading account with the international stockbroking partner of your Indian stockbroker and invest in foreign stocks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>2) You can directly open a trading account with an international stock broker</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">A few international stockbroking companies like Interactive Brokers, TD Ameritrade, and Charles Schwab International Account allow Indian citizens to directly open a trading account and to trade or invest in international stocks and funds.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Interactive Brokers LLC has an office in India. You can make a visit, and after getting all your queries answered, directly open your overseas trading account from the comfort of an office.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>3) Through financial mobile applications</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Many start-up investment firms like Grow, Vested Finance, and Webull have launched financial mobile applications that allow Indians and Non-Resident Indians (NRIs) to invest in foreign stocks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>4) Indirect international investments through Indian Mutual Funds or Exchange Traded Funds (ETFs)</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">There are a number of Mutual Funds and ETFs that invest in international equity markets. These funds are not only the easiest way to invest in foreign stocks but also the cheaper way to do it. You don&rsquo;t need an overseas trading account to invest through these funds.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">ICICI Prudential US Bluechip Equity, Motilal Oswal NASDAQ 100 ETF, and Nippon India US Equity Opportunities Fund are some of the popular mutual funds and ETFs that trade in global equities.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Some of the Indian stockbrokers like Zerodha are planning to set up facilities for their clients to directly invest in US and other international markets with no minimum investment. These yet-to-be launched facilities show the Indian stockbrokers&rsquo; efforts to cater to the rising enthusiasm of the Indian retail investors on international investments.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Crucial Factors To Consider Before Taking A Plunge Into International Investments</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">International investments don&rsquo;t come without any flaws or drawbacks. Here are a few crucial factors to consider before you invest in foreign stocks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>1) Higher Brokerage</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">When it comes to international investments, you will be transacting in foreign currencies. For instance, if you are investing in the US financial market, you have to pay the brokerages and taxes in the US dollar. Therefore, the brokerage, taxes and account maintenance fee may be a little higher compared to the brokerage, taxes and the maintenance fee of domestic trading accounts.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>2) Currency Risk</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">You should take into consideration the currency risk associated with international investments. Let&rsquo;s make the idea clear with the help of an example.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">When you bought a stock in the US stock market at the current currency exchange rate of $1= ₹74. However, when you sell the stock next year, the Indian currency may get stronger, and the currency exchange rate becomes $1 = ₹69.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">If that is the case, you have to bear the loss of the change in the currency rate along with the profit or loss of the stock&rsquo;s sale.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>3) There is a limit for overseas investments by an Individual resident Indian</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) notification in the Liberalised Remittance Scheme (LRS) points out a limit for an individual resident Indian for overseas investments. The limit is set at $250,000 per year. With the current exchange rate ($1= ₹74), this amount turns out to be roughly 19 million Indian rupees. Anyway, if you have four family members, you can invest 4 x 19 million Indian rupees. That constitutes around 76 million Indian Rupees.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>4) The macroeconomic trends in international markets.</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Besides the above-mentioned factors, you also need to keep in mind the unpredictable macroeconomic trends in international markets like the regional government policies along with political and economic trends that may affect the prices of foreign stocks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Final Words</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Stock market investments are always considered risky, but they can generate higher return in the long run than traditional fixed return generating investments. To reduce the investment risk, it&rsquo;s very important to diversify your portfolio among various stocks in different sectors rather than investing in just one stock or sector.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Investing in foreign stocks, without doubt, can generate higher returns and helps to diversify your portfolio. But you should also keep in mind that the Indian economy is one of the fastest growing economies in the world and most of the international markets are a little stagnant. It is always better to invest in an economy where growth takes place.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Justin Raj</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">​​​​​​​</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Alpha Research Team</span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937168/jyckicrqpl52mad2oxtp.webp","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"What Are Different Ways To Invest In International Equities?","seo_keywords":"What Are Different Ways To Invest In International Equities?","seo_description":"Have you ever thought of investing in globally leading innovative companies such as Apple, Google (Alphabet), Facebook, Amazon, Netflix, Microsoft, and Tesla? These international companies have greater growth potential and moreover, they are not listed in Indian stock exchanges like Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) or National Stock Exchange (NSE).","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937165/kdqrn1idjk2se5ikieqy.webp","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"133","title":"Are you an ESG Investor?","slug":"are-you-an-esg-investor","category":"General","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1635405979","published_date_view":"Oct 28, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">ESG Investing is gathering pace like never before. And as an aware investor, you must be mindful of the ABC of the ESG!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">ESG stands for environmental, social, and governance. The concept of ESG has been around for a long time, with its origins going back as far as 2005. UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan issued an ESG proposal submitted to the CEOs of the world&rsquo;s leading financial institutions. Annan invited the CEOs to join an initiative, later known as Principles for Responsible Investment, to tighten the relationship between investors and the ESG issues.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Today, over these years, ESG has gradually evolved as a tool for the&nbsp;management&nbsp;to deliver outstanding returns to all stakeholders of a business. Companies all over the globe have been sensitized about the various aspects of ESG. Stock exchanges&nbsp;across the world seek to report on ESG principles. At the same time, ESG compliance opens up doors for global funding for businesses across the globe.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">For a&nbsp;CEO, who cares about the long-term sustainability of the business, ESG is an opportunity to create value, drive profitability, and raise capital. ESG bonds have already made a mark in India, with Indian companies raising over $5 billion in the calendar year 2021 so far.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937284/cvt5zmralfmhldkvjpql.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 675px;\" type=\"image\" /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">ESG assets are set to reach over $50 trillion by 2025. According to&nbsp;Bloomberg, that&rsquo;s a third of total global assets under management.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Within the corporate environment, institutions are prioritizing their emphasis on ESG, moving beyond traditional corporate responsibility. Large financial institutions increasingly see ESG as corporate social responsibility.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The&nbsp;S&amp;P Global Market Intelligence&nbsp;analyzed 26 ESG exchange-traded funds and mutual funds with more than $250 million in assets under management. It found that from March 5, 2020, the month that the World Health Organization officially declared COVID-19 a pandemic, to March 5, 2021, 19 of those funds performed better than the S&amp;P 500.&nbsp;Those outperformers rose between 27.3% and 55% over that period. In comparison, the S&amp;P 500 increased just 27.1%. An ethical investment portfolio can actually protect you from risk while allowing you to make a positive impact.&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The pandemic highlighted social and global inequality. It also pushed millions into poverty. The&nbsp;World Bank calculates&nbsp;that COVID-19 sent around 97 million people into poverty in 2020, and the negative impact continues to weigh. The pandemic has been such an existential crisis &ndash; such a stark reminder of the world&rsquo;s fragility &ndash; that it has driven the world to confront the global threat of climate change more forcefully and to consider how, like the pandemic, it will alter lives across the globe.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">At the same time, the creation of sustainable index investments has enabled a massive acceleration of capital towards companies better prepared to address ESG factors. Indeed, from January through November 2020, investors in mutual funds and ETFs invested $288 billion globally in sustainable assets, a&nbsp;96% increase over the whole of 2019.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Initially, ESG investments had a reputation for generating limited returns. But, today, the data suggests that there is an intrinsic relationship between a company&rsquo;s ESG performance and long-term financial health. Traditional funds showed higher potential for loss during&nbsp;turbulent&nbsp;market years like 2008, 2009, 2015, and 2018, while sustainable funds posted strong performance.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">According to Bank of America, ESG investing could rise by $15 trillion to $20 trillion over the next decade because of changing demographics. As millennials, Gen-Z, and the generations to follow step into investor shoes, they are increasingly likely to select their portfolios based on companies that measure up to ESG metrics. The act of picking sustainable funds is reasonably intuitive due to&nbsp;respective companies being categorized by data providers. But despite this, it can be challenging to find a firm that fully subscribes to the ESG approach throughout.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Some advisers suggest that it&rsquo;s worth engaging with fund groups to see how companies deal with ESG issues in a bid to see whether they conform to a clear policy or not.&nbsp;Another positive comes from the fact that sustainable investing is growing in popularity today.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">With significant increases in social and environmental awareness worldwide, shares from ESG companies, in particular, look set to ride this wave of interest and grow exponentially as a result. If this occurs, then investors will benefit from gaining some sizeable profits from green companies along the way.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Of course, investing in ESG shares comes with a few downsides, too. By far, the most significant drawback comes from the lack of diversity offered by ESG shares. Sadly, most companies that fit the criteria focus exclusively on large-cap stocks, limiting the prospect of diversification among investor portfolios. Thus, investors may find themselves starved of exposure to small-cap, mid-cap and non-US based companies.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Another con is that some ESG mutual funds and ETFs and DIY investors develop strategies that entirely exclude specific industries, like tobacco and oil. While avoiding these industries is undoubtedly a good thing as far as the environmentally and socially conscious among us would agree, it only serves to enhance the risk of investors placing all their focus on very few industries &ndash; such as hydropower or electronic vehicles &ndash; which runs the risk of further diversification issues.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">For example, a heavily populated portfolio by wind-based energy suppliers is great in terms of adhering to sustainable investments. Still, investors could find themselves hamstrung if a windfarm is forced to close down or sanctions lower the global usage of wind power.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937311/tdduinr4wzdowmq0emc8.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 715px;\" type=\"image\" /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">So dear investors, it&rsquo;s important to remember that socially responsible investing is a highly subjective matter, and there&rsquo;s no guarantee that companies recognized as sustainable match your beliefs or investment goals.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">With this in mind, it&rsquo;s essential to conduct your research before buying shares or funds. Look for companies that match your ambitions and beliefs, and the act of investing in them will be its reward.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">With the rising sensitivity towards the environment and social issues, it would be prudent to grab a bite in the ESG pie in your investment portfolios. ESG investing is likely to have a robust future and are expected to beat the index returns in the near term.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;Best Regards</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;<br />\r\nDr. Tarunika Jain Agarwal Ph.D.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Alpha Research</span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937390/zcjibyvp4ihw78e3t5om.webp","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"Are you an ESG Investor?","seo_keywords":"Are you an ESG Investor?","seo_description":"ESG stands for environmental, social, and governance. The concept of ESG has been around for a long time, with its origins going back as far as 2005. UN Secretary-General Kofi Annan issued an ESG proposal submitted to the CEOs of the world’s leading financial institutions. Annan invited the CEOs to join an initiative, later known as Principles for Responsible Investment, to tighten the relationship between investors and the ESG issues.","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937388/vcv0otvtuc0m7nmucjdx.webp","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"135","title":"5 Charts – Interesting Stories on Markets and Investing (Research)","slug":"5-charts-interesting-stories-on-markets-and-investing-research-4","category":"General","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1635320255","published_date_view":"Oct 27, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Please find below the 5&nbsp;charts&nbsp;that tell interesting stories on Markets and Investing.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;<strong>1) Worried about Rising Good Prices?</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937941/zs6k1i4faypq2ubtvtpj.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 759px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Tighten your belt to face very high inflation in the next 12 months.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">As per new simulations by the IMF, in a worst case, headline inflation would peak next year at ~12% in advanced economies and ~25% in emerging market economies.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Due to supply side constraints and pent up demand, inflation is expected to rise significantly.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The good thing is that it will be transitory &amp; may last for ~12 months.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;<strong>2) The Great Interest Rate Normalization:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937964/azlysguzkqrbt4hndsoi.png\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 1475px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Global Central Banks have started increasing the interest rate due to rise in inflation.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">RBI has also announced normalization and has decided to start winding up additional liquidity from the system.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">This is good for fixed income asset class as expected return will go up.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Its suggested that the debt investors should stay invested in lower end of the yield curve to save themselves from interest rate volatility.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>3) Correlation between Inflation and Stock market Return:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937995/fsh7r5jtaoi2qtls16pv.png\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 787px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">There is no correlation between inflation and stock market return.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Even when inflation has been high in the past, the stock market has held up pretty well.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">That could be because the stock market is forward-looking.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">High inflation doesn&rsquo;t mean death sentence for the stock market.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>4) Valuation of Global Equity Markets:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687938025/jcb379ksnfvckrsqqumq.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 588px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Indian Equity Market is the most expensive globally. But thats how it has been always.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">2022 Forward PE Ratio for India is expected to be 23 against global average of 18 and US PE of 21.5.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The expected earnings growth for India is also among highest in the world.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>5) Falling Gold Demand in India:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687938050/r9kazlli5tb7cpnpapad.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 578px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Gold consumer demand (jewelry + bar + coins) in India has been falling continuously for the last 10 years.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Demonetization, mandatory PAN card, higher tax compliance have led to the softening of demand for gold.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Millennials moving away from gold is also impacting demand.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Best Regards</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Dr. Mukesh Jindal&nbsp;CFA, CFP, CAIA, Ph.D.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Alpha Research</span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687938187/c2ckav568mcw5p0sg107.png","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"5 Charts – Interesting Stories on Markets and Investing (Research)","seo_keywords":"5 Charts – Interesting Stories on Markets and Investing (Research)","seo_description":"As per new simulations by the IMF, in a worst case, headline inflation would peak next year at ~12% in advanced economies and ~25% in emerging market economies.","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687938184/h5izwdg2akglvup94rkn.png","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"134","title":"Bitcoin vs Gold – Analysis","slug":"bitcoin-vs-gold-analysis","category":"General","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1635319816","published_date_view":"Oct 27, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937487/e2kbv4we6l9wlrn2dr5g.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 718px;\" type=\"image\" /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The Corona pandemic has taught us many lessons that touched almost every aspect of our lives. But one of the most important one being about savings, financial planning, and investments. It was the financial lifestyle of the ones who made wise and calculated financial decisions that was left unscathed during this tough phase of the global economic meltdown.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">It is worth noting that during this trying period, we have witnessed investors move their assets to safe havens. We have seen the crumbling down of traditional business models and the rise of New Age investments such as cryptocurrencies and digital assets.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&lsquo;An investment in gold will save you in difficult times.&rsquo; It has been a powerful age-old wisdom for Indians. According to the World Gold Council&rsquo;s (WGC) estimate, approximately 25,000 tonnes of gold has been accumulated by the Indians households; that is, roughly 12.65% of nearly 2 lakh tonnes of the yellow metal mined throughout human history!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Traditionally, investments in gold have generated good returns. It has been an intelligent investment move to hedge the volatility of the stock market with gold. But with the advent of cryptocurrency that has generated even better returns than gold, the yellow metal&rsquo;s lustre has been diminishing. Thus, Bitcoin, the most popular cryptocurrency, is the new hot cake just taken out of the oven.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>The Factors Favouring Gold</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The precious yellow metal is highly valuable and limited in supply regardless of the demand. It is a high in demand raw material for consumer goods such as jewellery and a stable investment vehicle.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">While a company can issue new shares, and a central bank can print fiat currency, gold can&rsquo;t be manufactured to meet the demand. It must be mined and processed.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Above everything else, central banks issue fiat currency on the gold standard.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>The Factors Favouring Cryptocurrency</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Bitcoin, a cryptocurrency run on Blockchain technology, shares some properties with gold. Since Bitcoin is not linked with other traditional assets such as stocks or stock market, many have termed Bitcoin as &lsquo;digital gold&rsquo; of the 21<sup>st</sup>&nbsp;century.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">As a storage of value, Bitcoin has marked a great improvement over gold and the post-pandemic world has taken it into consideration and began to track cryptocurrencies in real-time. Last few months have witnessed Bitcoin&rsquo;s value increase multifold and it is likely to continue appreciating in monetary terms over the coming years.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">In fact, gold underperformed Bitcoin for the last decade. Bitcoin has generated an annual return of around 230% in the last 10 years while gold could provide an average return of 12-14% to the investors. It has been estimated that by 2030 Bitcoin&rsquo;s market capitalization will surpass gold&rsquo;s. Bitcoin crossed the $1 trillion market capitalization mark in February 2020.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The Millennials and the Generation Z (Gen Z) do most of their financial transactions virtually and they are not too much attached to the tangibility of the assets they hold. Bitcoin and other cryptocurrencies have given them access to a digital asset that can be, in the long run, more rewarding than Gold.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Gold And Cryptocurrency &ndash; A Comparison</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Both Bitcoin and gold are rare in terms of supply but in the terms of transparency, legality, and safety, gold outsmarts cryptocurrency.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Gold and Bitcoin are liquid assets but both diverge when it comes to volatility. Bitcoin is much more volatile than gold. The precious yellow metal also holds a long history of being a less volatile investment vehicle than a cryptocurrency like Bitcoin.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The world of cryptocurrency is surrounded by speculations, rumours, and abrupt market crashes. The major number of the crypto investors belong to the rich class who possess higher technological knowledge. But for gold, it is not the case. Anyone belongs to any economic class and any level of technological knowledge has access to the traditional gold market.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">It has been anticipated for years that gold&rsquo;s supply will end one day. But in reality, its supply has eventually increased, though not in accordance with the demand. Still today, there exists many unexplored gold mines in various parts of the world, and we are not sure of how much gold is still waiting to be explored.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The supply of Bitcoin is entirely different. Roughly 97% of Bitcoins has been mined till date, that is, around 19 million of the limits of 21 million.&nbsp; It has been estimated that the last bitcoin will be mined by 2140.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Food For An Investment Thought</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The primary intention of this article is to bring out the merits and demerits of both gold and Bitcoin. By now, you are aware of the roles gold and Bitcoin play in today&rsquo;s financial world. Now it is the time to take a little thought on how to take these assets into consideration as investments.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The governments and regulatory bodies all over the globe are still mulling over regulating the cryptocurrency markets. Hence, till a consensus has been reached, it should be very important not to allow greed or the lure of higher returns drive your investment decisions. The returns of the investments and the safety of the capital depends on the sole discretion of an investor where he or she wants to invest and how he or she wants to do it.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">According to financial experts, both assets are often seen either as a diversification tool in a portfolio or as a hedge against inflation. It is always advisable to have a balanced portfolio. Even when it comes to cryptocurrency investment, keeping a balanced investment approach is a must.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The expert suggestion is that though investments in Bitcoin doesn&rsquo;t come with any limits, it would be wise not to put all your savings, or emergency fund in it. Some experts suggest that the investments in cryptocurrency should not exceed more than 5 percent of your portfolio.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">As you have seen, gold and Bitcoin have different roles to play as an asset. So, an investor must, first of all, assess his or her risk appetite and then strategically diversify the investment portfolio. It is also advisable to seek assistance from financial advisors before making such investment decisions. An investor should learn the basics of investing and do their own unbiased research before taking a plunge into cryptocurrency investing.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Justin Raj</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Alpha Research Team</span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937771/irwlyg4v2d5p3k85yff3.webp","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"Bitcoin vs Gold – Analysis","seo_keywords":"Bitcoin vs Gold – Analysis","seo_description":"The Corona pandemic has taught us many lessons that touched almost every aspect of our lives. But one of the most important one being about savings, financial planning, and investments. It was the financial lifestyle of the ones who made wise and calculated financial decisions that was left unscathed during this tough phase of the global economic meltdown.","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687937769/yvmo7fvkogyokkonwdmb.webp","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"136","title":"How To Beat a Nobel Prize Portfolio?","slug":"how-to-beat-a-nobel-prize-portfolio","category":"General","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1634888624","published_date_view":"Oct 22, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">If you are an investor guided by a financial advisor or a solo investor who makes investment decisions on your own, you may know about Modern Portfolio Theory (MPT) put forward by Harry Markowitz, an American economist.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">In 1990, Markowitz was awarded the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences for his Modern Portfolio Theory. The Nobel Prize winning theory defends a diversified, or an &lsquo;optimal&rsquo; portfolio. That is, a portfolio that allocates assets to maximize return by taking up a quantifiable amount of risk. In other words, a quantitative risk assessment method could be implemented along with diversification and calculated asset allocation to bring down investment risk.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><b>Nobel Prize Portfolio in a Nutshell&nbsp;</b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Modern Portfolio Theory, proposed by Markowitz initially as a research paper to build a portfolio of assets to deliver maximum returns with a stipulated level of risk, was first published by the Journal of Finance in 1952. A portfolio built on Modern Portfolio Theory is also known as the Nobel Prize Portfolio.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Prior to Harry Markowitz&rsquo;s Modern Portfolio Theory, the returns from investing were largely calculated in terms of the performance of an individual investment. Markowitz demonstrated that the collective performance of the assets in a portfolio is more significant in generating returns than the performance of a particular asset or stock.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">A portfolio with diversified investment classes and financial instruments has lower correlation to each other. That means, their performance and returns vary in accordance with different stock market cycles and macroeconomic conditions. This variety in investment classes and securities reduces the volatility of a portfolio and guards it against unexpected financial market shocks.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The quantitative risk analysis method of a Nobel Prize Portfolio uses the past data on investment risk and returns along with the expected investment returns in future. It also takes into consideration the investor preferences to build an optimised portfolio of assets that delivers the higher returns at the lowest possible risk.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><b>Shortcomings of a Nobel Prize Portfolio</b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The major shortcoming of a Nobel Prize Portfolio is the complexity associated with its mathematical model. The quantitative risk analysis method of MPT is based on the evaluation of historical investment returns and volatility. That means, the portfolio can be highly vulnerable to unknown variables in the future or the ones investors fail to consider during the time of creating the equation. This risk analysis method based on projected values and predictive mathematical calculations is far from reality and fails to deal with the risks in the real investment world. In other words, the investing process may appear orderly using the mathematical risk assessment model of MPT; yet, in reality, it makes a probabilistic risk assessment, not a structural one.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">In the late 1970s, a researcher named Sanjay Basu demonstrated&nbsp;something contrary to the Modern Portfolio Theory: low price-to-earnings ratio (P/E) stocks outperform high P/E stocks. In the early 1980s, Rolf Banz, another finance scholar, demonstrated&nbsp;that small capitalization (small cap) stocks outperformed large capitalization (large cap) stocks. His theory is popularly known as Small Firm Effect.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">This is another reason &ndash; apart from abiding by the Securities and Exchange Bureau of India (SEBI) guidelines &ndash; most investment firms never fail to note &lsquo;past performance does not necessarily predict future results&rsquo; in the documentation of their investment products.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">There is a greater irony: The father of Nobel prize winning Modern Portfolio Theory never trusted his brainchild when building his portfolio. Jason Zweig, a well-known financial journalist, mentioned this in his bestselling book Your Money and Your Brains. Here is the excerpt from the book &ndash; an expert in linear programming, he [Harry Markowitz] knows that &ldquo;I should have computed the historical co-variances of the asset classes and drawn an efficient frontier. Instead, I visualized my grief if the stock market went way up, and I wasn&rsquo;t in it &mdash; or if it went way down and I was completely in it. My intention was to minimize my future regret. So, I split my contributions 50/50 between bonds and equities&rdquo;.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Why did Harry Markowitz choose an equal weightage asset allocation in his portfolio? Why did he avoid his Nobel Prize winning investment theory?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The answer is quite simple: He chose simplicity over complexity.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><b>Simplicity Is the Key</b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">According to Albert Einstein, &ldquo;if you can&rsquo;t explain it simply, you don&rsquo;t understand it well enough.&rdquo;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Einstein is right both in scientific and investment terms. In the world of finance, simple investment theories and practices always have an upper hand over sophisticated strategies and theories. A simple investment strategy is the best strategy an investor can ever adopt.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Nevertheless, the human mind always hunts for complexity and sophistication as we believe that only through sophisticated investment strategies, we can beat the market. Investors, especially the ones with larger capital allocation, fall prey to his terrible investment mistake.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Even market pundits are not saved from this trap. The market genius who talks nonstop about the future of the stock market or particular securities makes us believe that he or she knows everything about the financial markets and the investment world. But in reality, they are simple humans with sophisticated investment strategies. Most of them don&rsquo;t know what they don&rsquo;t know and their job demands giving out careless opinions and comments on both finance and non-finance matters.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Just take a few seconds to think, how many of these experts predicted the CoVID spread and subsequent financial market downturns all over the globe? How many of them successfully predicted the bullish market trends in the financial markets all over the world soon after the turmoil?&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The purpose of this article is not to question Harry Markowitz&rsquo;s Nobel Prize Portfolio or to blame market pundits. Here, the objective is to shed some light on no matter the level of our expertise, we fail miserably to predict the unknown future. As investors, we may have solutions to known investment risks, but when unknown risks are concerned, we render clueless. Every investment theory, including MPT, may guard us against known risks but, unfortunately, not against unknown risks.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><b>Bottom Line</b></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Diversification and calculated capital allocation are the best hedges against unknown risks. A solid hedge against complexity is always simplicity. Never confuse yourself with the sophisticated investment strategies proposed by your financial planner or portfolio manager. Always remember that complexity damages your hard-earned capital. Simplify your investment strategies and invest only in the stocks of the businesses that are simple to understand.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Justin Raj</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Alpha Research Team</span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687938376/omlpzvoxoikvo9uz2tjz.webp","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"How To Beat a Nobel Prize Portfolio?","seo_keywords":"How To Beat a Nobel Prize Portfolio?","seo_description":"In 1990, Markowitz was awarded the Nobel Memorial Prize in Economic Sciences for his Modern Portfolio Theory. The Nobel Prize winning theory defends a diversified, or an ‘optimal’ portfolio. That is, a portfolio that allocates assets to maximize return by taking up a quantifiable amount of risk. In other words, a quantitative risk assessment method could be implemented along with diversification and calculated asset allocation to bring down investment risk.","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687938374/hcjyw9ylszrher1l3lpv.webp","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"137","title":"5 Charts – Interesting Stories on Markets and Investing (Research)","slug":"5-charts-interesting-stories-on-markets-and-investing-research-3","category":"General","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1634632437","published_date_view":"Oct 19, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><strong>1) Balance sheet analysis of Indian companies:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941452/jaevvpouilysjdaxxs1m.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 422px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">1) Debt to Equity ratio of 0.16 is at a historical low</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">2) Earning Yield/ Bond Yield is positive after 11 years</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">3) CFO/ PAT of 1.4 is at an all time high</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Indicators suggest that company balance sheets are strong &amp; share prices can go up.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>2) Returns in stock market are a chaotic mess:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941476/bxumzrpppabydnfg312y.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 840px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">It is impossible to predict what next year&rsquo;s returns are going to be.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The above chart plots the US S&amp;P 500&rsquo;s annual returns since 1926.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Equity market in long term may give average return of 15% but in short term it can be extremely volatile.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">The good news is that majority of the dots are in positive zone.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>3) Indian Mid Cap valuation:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941508/ibllflxipxozyogzgemx.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 914px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">From a valuation perspective, mid caps look relatively attractive over the large caps.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">During the bull phase in 2017, mid caps had traded at a 45% premium to large caps.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Since Nov&rsquo;20, small and mid caps have picked up steam and may hopefully deliver good returns for few more quarters.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>4) Tech stocks correction due to rise&nbsp;of interest rate:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941538/upni4xcq1lalbgh4nran.png\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 784px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">There is lot of noise around tech stocks correcting due to rise of interest rates.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">This fear may be unfounded because historically there is no correlation between tech stocks and interest rate.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Empirically, the correlation is -0.1 which means no relationship.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"color:#c0392b;\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>5) Affordability ratio for buying a house:</strong></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941560/b7hxplysgmi2wuylynxk.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 969px;\" type=\"image\" /></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Affordability Ratio &ndash; Home Loan Payment/ Income Ratio is at the best point in the last 21 years.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Good time to buy house for self use.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Residential real estate should start seeing good traction. This will be good for overall economy as demand for cement, steel, paint &amp; labour will go up.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Read more similar articles in our blog &ndash;&nbsp;<a data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?q=https://click.mlsend.com/link/c/YT0xNzk5MjM2MTI0OTQ2NzMxOTU3JmM9cTdrNCZlPTExMTcxNzI1JmI9NzYwODgwOTYzJmQ9cDhsNHE5dg%3D%3D.OnRPTj4w6VSZ7BIAlNjT7OFcFxsv022YXnwNsVmM_wQ&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1634698539776000&amp;usg=AFQjCNEPPlI5vAm3al2bwn59nv665bBb2A\" href=\"https://click.mlsend.com/link/c/YT0xNzk5MjM2MTI0OTQ2NzMxOTU3JmM9cTdrNCZlPTExMTcxNzI1JmI9NzYwODgwOTYzJmQ9cDhsNHE5dg==.OnRPTj4w6VSZ7BIAlNjT7OFcFxsv022YXnwNsVmM_wQ\">https://alphacapital.in/blog/</a></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Best Regards</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">&nbsp;Dr. Mukesh Jindal&nbsp;CFA, CFP, CAIA, Ph.D.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">Alpha Research</span></p>\r\n","is_active":"1","is_draft":"0","blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941679/ssptavebg3qdwhgmmelj.webp","published_by_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687758943/o9rxxf4fosnurb23hjsv.png","seo_title":"5 Charts – Interesting Stories on Markets and Investing (Research)","seo_keywords":"5 Charts – Interesting Stories on Markets and Investing (Research)","seo_description":"1) Debt to Equity ratio of 0.16 is at a historical low\r\n\r\n2) Earning Yield/ Bond Yield is positive after 11 years\r\n\r\n3) CFO/ PAT of 1.4 is at an all time high","seo_blog_image":"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941677/mfgcna2jvsqldhytzonv.webp","created_at":"Jun 28, 2023"},{"blog_id":"138","title":"HDFC Life Sanchay Plus – Analysis & Review","slug":"hdfc-life-sanchay-plus","category":"Investment Ideas","published_by":"Alpha Research","published_date":"1634546497","published_date_view":"Oct 18, 2021","discription":"<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><input alt=\"\" src=\"http://res.cloudinary.com/dyedkdjm1/image/upload/v1687941771/zjdac1khrtkphjxhpyl7.webp\" style=\"width: 1080px; height: 888px;\" type=\"image\" /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">HDFC Life Sanchay Plus is the most popular insurance product, which esteemed Bank HDFC is selling for the past 3 years on &amp; on. It is non-participating traditional Insurance plan with a very good explanation attached to it, which says &ndash;&nbsp;<strong>You fetch guaranteed income and return of principal at maturity. Both post tax.</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">For example &ndash; You pay 25 Lac for 6 years and then 8<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;year you will start 11.3 lac per annum for next 30 year &amp; at maturity take your 25 L x 6 = 1.5 crore back too. Everything post tax.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">I would like to ask readers &ndash; How does it sounds?&nbsp;<em>Fabulous &amp; Stupendous and Plan is easy to understand</em>. Investors will appreciate that but whether return are good or bad is different matter altogether. This is because we cannot calculate the Time value of money for such long years verbally. Therefore we put pen &amp; paper at work (Nowadays Excel) to calculate the actual CAGR of product. Following are the results:-</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table width=\"243\">\r\n\t<tbody>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"44\">&nbsp;</td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Date</strong></span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"101\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\"><strong>Plan 1</strong></span></td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"44\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">1</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">11/10/21</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"101\">\r\n\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">-2500000</span></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"44\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">2</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">11/10/22</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"101\">\r\n\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">-2500000</span></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"44\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">3</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">11/10/23</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"101\">\r\n\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">-2500000</span></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"44\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">4</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">11/10/24</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"101\">\r\n\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">-2500000</span></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"44\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">5</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"97\"><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">11/10/25</span></td>\r\n\t\t\t<td width=\"101\">\r\n\t\t\t<p><span style=\"font-size:20px;\">-2500000</span></p>\r\n\t\t\t</td>\r\n\t\t</tr>\r\n\t\t<tr>\